.TH "fsverity_ioctl_measure" 9 "fsverity_ioctl_measure" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fsverity_ioctl_measure \- get a verity file's digest
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" fsverity_ioctl_measure
.BI "(struct file *filp "  ","
.BI "void __user *_uarg "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "filp" 12
file to get digest of
.IP "_uarg" 12
user pointer to fsverity_digest
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Retrieve the file digest that the kernel is enforcing for reads from a verity
file.  See the "FS_IOC_MEASURE_VERITY" section of
Documentation/filesystems/fsverity.rst for the documentation.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, -errno on failure
